            <provenance>
              The manuscript possibly belonged to <persName ref="PRS9683Urbino">Giusto da Urbino</persName>.
              According to the account on the manuscripts’ provenance given by Tisserant, this manuscript is among those
              acquired by <persName ref="PRS4805Grebaut" role="owner"/> in <placeName ref="LOC1216AddisA">ʾAddis ʾAbabā</placeName> 
              in <date when="1925"/> with funds of
              <persName ref="PRS14055SaintJ">Jean Saint</persName>. 
              The manuscripts originated from Šawā (ʾAddis ʾAbabā, Dabra Libānos, Dabra Bǝrhān),
              Goǧǧām (Dimā Giyorgis, Marṭula Māryām, Dabra Warq) and Bagemdǝr (Gondar, ʾAzazo Takla Hāymānot) and very few from Tǝgrāy.
